Package: dany
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: Concurrent typed-ANY DNS lookup utility (+ NXDOMAIN prober)
 dany simulates the (unreliable / semi-deprecated) DNS ANY query by firing
 the configured RR types (default SOA,NS,A,AAAA,MX,TXT) concurrently against
 a single hostname and aggregating the responses. Optional flags add PTR
 enrichment for A/AAAA results, well-known underscore-subdomain probes
 (_dmarc, _domainkey, _mta-sts), and a www.<host> probe. Output may be
 rendered as tab-separated text (default), JSON, or YAML.
 .
 dnx, included in the same package, reads hostnames from arguments or stdin
 and reports the subset that return NXDOMAIN across all of MX, NS, and SOA
 (a conservative "this name truly doesn't exist" check). Runs lookups
 concurrently with configurable parallelism.
 .
 Distributed as pure-Go statically-linked executables (CGO disabled) with
 no shared-library or NSS resolver dependencies.
